<p><strong>Bug A</strong> — This should draw a ship in any colour, but every ship comes out the same colour no matter what you pass in.</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">def draw_ship(x, body_color, size=1):
    pygame.draw.rect(screen, GREEN, (x - 20, HEIGHT - 120, 40, 50))
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> the function ignores its own <code>body_color</code> parameter.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

