<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug C</strong> — You want most ships to stay normal size without typing <code>size=1</code> every time, but right now leaving size out causes an error.</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">def draw_ship(x, body_color, size):
    ...

draw_ship(400, RED)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> give <code>size</code> a default value so it can be left out.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code (just the <code>def</code> line):</strong></p>
